and science fiction movies. Früchtl takes a clear position within the ongoing discussion in the humanities and social sciences about modernity, a discussion that, in light of the work of Foucault, Lyotard, and Habermas, has too often neglected the importance of Romanticism. Similarly, he embraces the role of film and popular culture in modern society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aCinema and Media Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aPhilosophy -- Poststructuralism and Phenomenology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362680540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626805423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626805/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles